other_tests.findings: Sinus rhythm, heart rate 103 bpm, AQRS +120, deep S in D1, late R in AVR, and the presence of qR waves in V1. Asymmetrical inversion of ST segment and T wave from V1 to V4.
Pulmonary artery systolic pressure of 120 mm Hg, a dilated right ventricle, and paradoxical movement of the septum.
TAPSE of 13 mm, interatrial communication of 17 mm diameter upper venous sinus type, and right to left shunt. Both pulmonary right veins drained to the lower vena cava in a supradiaphagmatic portion.
Confirmed the previous diagnosis of severe pulmonary hypertension that is not responsive to vasodilator challenge.
